Program: Outlook
Title: Dr Juan Romagoza
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbs6h
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
El Salvadorian doctor Dr Juan Romagoza on surviving torture and his work as the director of La Clinica Del Pueblo. Also, a soundscape tour of Phnom Penh, Cambodia. How 7 women survived the Rwandan genocide by hiding in a bathroom for 3 months. Presenter: Frederick Dove.